hasPersistentData

public boolean hasPersistentData()
Checks to see if the event contains information about persistent objects/attributes. A variety of checks are performed, depending on the type of the event.

If the source object class is not PERSISTENT, we return false.

If it's a CREATE event, we check to see if any of the attributes (beyond the objectClass) are PERSISTENT, if so, we return true.

If it's a DELETE event, we return true.

If it's a MODIFIED event, we check the modify attribute. If it refers to any PERSISTENT attribute, we return true.

Returns:
true if there's persistent data and false otherwise.

getSlice

public DMPEvent getSlice(DmcSliceInfo dsi)
This method will slice the event appropriately, depending on the type of event and the specified slice.

If this is a MODIFIED event, we will check to see if any of the attributes in the modifier are associated with the specified slice. If so, a new DMPEvent is returned that has the modifier sliced to contain only changes associated with the slice. If not, null is returned.

If this is a CREATED/LOADED event, we slice the object for the required attributes and return a new DMPEvent with that information. NOTE: we always return a new event, even if all we have is the name of the object.

Parameters:
dsi -
Returns:
a sliced event with the appropriate attributes.
